p=0.00). On the other hand, the increase of the standardized disability-adjusted 
life year rate was related to musculoskeletal disorders, diabetes, kidney 
disorders and substance use disorders with a significant annual percentage 
change of 0.1%, 0.2% and 1.3% (p=0.00) respectively. Conclusion: the 
implementation of the national strategy is the key solution to mitigate the 
impact of non-communicable diseases in Tunisia.

